description: This column is about storing the description of the public channels within the messaging and collaboration platform. It could include details such as the purpose, topic, guidelines, or rules for the channel.

This column is about storing the file names of attachments related to messages within the messaging and collaboration platform. These file names could include documents, images, videos, or other types of files shared by users within the platform.
This column is about storing the type of file attached to messages in the messaging and collaboration platform. It could include file formats such as images, documents, videos, etc.

This column is about storing the unique identifiers (S3 keys) for the attachments uploaded by users in messages within the messaging and collaboration platform. These S3 keys are used to retrieve and display the attachments within the platform.
This column contains the emojis used as reactions to messages within the messaging and collaboration platform. Users can react to messages with various emojis to express their emotions or responses.

examples: Hi there! Are we still on for our meeting tomorrow?

description: This column is about storing the actual message content sent by users within the messaging and collaboration platform. It may include text, emojis, attachments, or other multimedia content shared by users in the platform.

This column is about storing the names of migrations in the public schema of the database. Migrations are scripts or files that help manage changes to the database schema over time, such as creating new tables or altering existing ones. Each record in this column would likely represent a specific migration file or script used in the platform's development and maintenance process.

This column is about storing the usernames of users who are registered on the messaging and collaboration platform. Usernames are unique identifiers for each user and are used for authentication and identification purposes within the platform.
This column is about storing the email addresses of users who are registered on the messaging and collaboration platform.
This column is about storing the hashed passwords of users for security purposes in the messaging and collaboration platform.
This column is about storing the URL of the avatar image associated with a user's profile in the messaging and collaboration platform.

This column is about the roles that users have within a specific workspace. It could include roles such as 'admin', 'member', or 'guest' which determine the permissions and access level the user has within that workspace.

This column is about storing the names of the workspaces within the messaging and collaboration platform. Each record in this column would represent a unique workspace that users can join to collaborate and communicate with others.

description: This column is about storing the description of workspaces in the messaging and collaboration platform. Workspaces are virtual spaces where users can collaborate, communicate, and share information. The descriptions provide a brief overview or details about the purpose, goals, or topics of the workspace to help users understand its context and content.
